CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774210270
OL,3,CPM to chair Cobra meeting as Iran war
OL,4,Cthreatens cost of living crisis
OL,6,FThe government has already been forced
OL,7,Fto act since the war began because of
OL,8,Fthe spike in oil and gas prices,
OL,9,Fproviding #53 million to help the most
OL,10,Fvulnerable deal with the increasing
OL,11,Fcost of heating oil.
OL,13,FAround 1.5 million households rely on
OL,14,Fheating oil, but the price isn't
OL,15,Fcapped by the regulator Ofgem, so they
OL,16,Fwere more exposed to the sudden jump.
OL,18,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,19,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,20,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,21,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774210270
OL,3,CPM to chair Cobra meeting as Iran war
OL,4,Cthreatens cost of living crisis
OL,6,FNow, there is wider concern about the
OL,7,Fimpact of the conflict on our pockets,
OL,8,Fwith warnings that typical household
OL,9,Fenergy bills could increase by #332 a
OL,10,Fyear in July, according to consultancy
OL,11,FCornwall Insight.
OL,13,FAlthough the government points out
OL,14,Fthat energy bills will come down in
OL,15,FApril, the prediction of a steep rise
OL,16,Fin the summer is heaping pressure on
OL,17,Fthose at the top to announce some sort
OL,18,Fof support package for people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774210270
OL,3,CPM to chair Cobra meeting as Iran war
OL,4,Cthreatens cost of living crisis
OL,6,FWhen I asked Housing Secretary Steve
OL,7,FReed what that might look like, he
OL,8,Ftold me: "I can't tell you what's
OL,9,Fgoing to happen in three days' time,
OL,10,Flet alone three months' time.
OL,12,F"We'll keep the situation under
OL,13,Freview, and as you saw with heating
OL,14,Foil, where there is a requirement for
OL,15,Fthe government to step in, we did."
OL,17,FThe meeting on Monday is one of many
OL,18,Fbeing held as this situation develops,
OL,19,Fso there are no promises it will
OL,20,Fprompt a significant update.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774210270
OL,3,CPM to chair Cobra meeting as Iran war
OL,4,Cthreatens cost of living crisis
OL,6,FOne policy the government does not
OL,7,Fsupport, is introducing a temporary
OL,8,Fprofit cap for energy producers and
OL,9,Fretailers, as suggested by their 'cost
OL,10,Fof living champion'.
OL,12,FLabour peer Richard Walker, the chair
OL,13,Fof Iceland, wrote in the Sunday Times
OL,14,Fthat he had asked the government to
OL,15,F"consider a temporary profit cap, if
OL,16,Frequired, to stop producers and
OL,17,Fretailers exploiting the crisis to
OL,18,Fmake windfall profits at the expense
OL,19,Fof consumers".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774210270
OL,3,CPM to chair Cobra meeting as Iran war
OL,4,Cthreatens cost of living crisis
OL,6,F"It's always interesting to hear what
OL,7,Fhe's saying," Steve Reed said.
OL,9,FBut, he added: "Lord Walker is
OL,10,Fentitled to his view, that's not
OL,11,Fcurrently government policy."
OL,13,FThe government is hoping for a swift
OL,14,Fresolution to this conflict and when
OL,15,Fyou look at the problems it is already
OL,16,Fcausing ministers, you can understand
OL,17,Fwhy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
